article.headline: Michigan 51, Boston U. 46
article.story: BOSTON (AP)-- Daniel Horton scored 21 points, including a pair of free throws with 11.8 seconds left, to lead Michigan past Boston University 51-46 on Tuesday night. Michigan (2-0), which lost to BU (0-2) at home in each of the last two seasons, held the Terriers to the second-lowest point total by a Wolverines opponent since they beat Wisconsin 51-39 in 1999. With Michigan ahead by five, Brian Macon hit a 3-pointer to bring the Terriers within 48-46 with 13.2 seconds remaining. Horton then hit two free throws to make it a two-possession game. BU freshman Corey Hassan missed a 3-pointer with 3.9 seconds left. Hassan brought Boston University within 46-43 on a 3-pointer with 2:02 left. Horton scored baskets on three straight possessions to give Michigan its largest lead of the second half, 44-35, with 3:35 to play. Michigan led by as much as 17-8 midway through the first half before BU rallied to get within 23-22. Despite committing 13 turnovers and five offensive fouls in the first half, Michigan led 26-22 at halftime. Kevin Gardner led BU with 12 points and 11 rebounds. Macon added 10 points. Lester Abram scored 10 points for Michigan, which attempted 25 foul shots to just seven for the Terriers.
